column16: Description
Playing with the dogs
Have been told I rolled off a bed and broke my hip - Aunt called CPS. Unknown what actually happened. Had surgery.
Making more friends. Going to school.
Brothers caught by police stealing bikes. Dad made us watch him make a paddle out of a 2x4 because of this.
Sister said my mom beat her up so she ran away to AZ.
Brother got sent off to military school
Bullied at school by popular girls. Led to physical fights at school.
Brother moving out of house - would take me to do fun activities
Got suspended for taking alcohol to school and getting all my friend drunk. 1 week suspension.
Parents divorce - they didn't talk about it
Started selling drugs

Cop had been harassing me (following me all over the place). Pulled me over for no seatbelt; searched car; found a small bag of dope and cigarettes. He let me go. Had to do a first time offenders course but no jail time. Later sued the cop for harassment - no outcome. He left me alone after that.
Moving out of parents house
Gang violence at apartments - fights and gun violence
Graduated high school
Childs father forced me to manufacture drugs - even while pregnant. He was pure chaos; he was high all the time; very manipulative; mostly mental abuse but some physical
Daughter born
Got daughter into private Christian school
Took trip to Hawaii with drug money with daughter and daughters father
Watched someone try to commit suicide by shooting himself in the face - he lived. Held his face and called ambulance.
Getting and Staying in apartment in CityD

Started working closely with gang members - selling guns and stolen vehicles also cooking and selling meth. Found out later that police starting to watch me during this time. I was making really good money and my daughter was happy despite what was happening. It was amazing to be away from her dad.

After leaving daughters father had to hide out for 6 months in a cabin on a side of a hill because he was threatening to kill me. Still selling and cooking drugs but trying to find place for daughter and job.
Met a sober guy - he was great. First sober person I ever really met.

Being watched and instead of paying bills started doing more illegal things. Got evicted from apartment --> took daughter to her grandma and asked her to take care of her. Started living out of stolen cars or in hotel rooms or at friends houses if I cooked for them.

Search warrant for hotel room - meth-lab guns etc. Arrested but friends bailed me out. I stole a car on the way out and sold it to pay off attorney. I went on the run until 2013 - avoiding court dates and hiding out from warrants. Looking back this was the thing that changed trajectory of my life and in hindsight is a good event (mood rating = 7)
Son Born
Having an open relationship with my daughter. She is dealing with mental health and we are able to talk about it
Friend and I moved out of shelter and got rental home together
Going on vacations with friends and family
Coaching kids soccer team and cross-country
Bought my home
